genresAdvancedInfo.name: metal gaucho
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Originating in Argentina, Metal Gaucho is a blend of heavy metal with traditional Argentine folk music, specifically the music of the gauchos (cowboys). It features the use of instruments such as the charango, bombo, and accordion, along with distorted guitars and fast drumming. The lyrics often touch upon the history, traditions, and struggles of the gauchos, as well as social and political issues.
